		[MEDIUM PRIORITY] 

- Usare il multipath per i gnode. Ad esempio se un bnode e' collegato con piu'
  nodi di uno stesso gnode esterno li deve mettere come nexthop nella stessa rotta 
  per raggiungere il gnode esterno. Se ci sono tanti bnode per raggiungere uno
  stesso gnode, bisogna usare sempre il multipath.

- The QSPN has to remove the died nodes after QSPN_WAIT*2 seconds.

- ANDNA Backup_gnodes. Really necessary?

- Anti spoof Hook: a node must not give the maps to a node, which is trying to
  use an ip of another gnode.

- Aaah, do all the big endian/little endian stuff for the int and short in
  the packets.

- Port the kernel route code for *BSD: take a look at rt_ioctl.c and
  rt_socket.c of quagga.
  
- API for the maps sync with the netsukuku_d daemon.

- Write the documentation for the code that can be used by other
  programs. (By the way it is already commented.)


		[LOW PRIORITY]

- Test request.c

gmap.c: Optimize random_ip() to return valid IPs. A possible solution would be
	to zero all the invalid bits.
hook.c: Optimize the space of the free_node pkt: instead using an array of
	u_char for each free node, use just one bit and set it to one or zero.
	Use the nice functions of set_bit, clear_bit..., is_set, in
	asm/bitops.h.
broadcast: Tenere in considerazione il gttl.
hook.c:	Flush all the routes present in the routing table before starting the
